 September 2025 to 12 May 2026. She was elected as the MP for Barking in July 2024.</p>\n","image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/68be8776b0a373a01819ff09/s465_Nesil_Caliskan_960.jpeg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T20:23:23Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Nesil Caliskan MP","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/nesil-caliskan","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","base_path":"/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","content_id":"dd4e6468-e7a9-4259-8524-29599794c2b7","details":{"body":"\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":4,"whip_organisation":{"label":"House of Commons","sort_order":1}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T20:45:41Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T20:25:00Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Nesil Caliskan MP - Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"fe3986fe-03ad-45d2-9118-3f199009f966","details":{"current":false,"ended_on":"2025-09-06T00:00:00+01:00","person_appointment_order":1,"started_on":"2024-07-10T00:00:00+01:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/chris-elmore","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/chris-elmore","base_path":"/government/people/chris-elmore","content_id":"739e6ec2-1179-4596-8a39-9dc9459c9496","details":{"body":"<p>Chris Elmore was appointed Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State in the Foreign, Commonwealth and Development Office on 7 September 2025. He was previously Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) between 10 July 2024 and 7 September 2025. He was elected as the MP for Bridgend in July 2024.</p>\n","image":{"alt_text":"Chris Elmore MP","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/68d68aa29cb44667f7a1cecc/s465_AR109629.jpg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-09-07T14:38:24Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Chris Elmore MP","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/chris-elmore","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","base_path":"/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","content_id":"dd4e6468-e7a9-4259-8524-29599794c2b7","details":{"body":"\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":4,"whip_organisation":{"label":"House of Commons","sort_order":1}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T20:45:41Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-09-07T14:33:06Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Chris Elmore MP - Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"ab388f97-edd8-4d25-9754-b44bc0c613a1","details":{"current":false,"ended_on":"2024-07-05T00:00:00+01:00","person_appointment_order":3,"started_on":"2022-07-07T00:00:00+01:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/rebecca-harris","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/rebecca-harris","base_path":"/government/people/rebecca-harris","content_id":"0cf103ff-8ecf-4d61-b3ef-9323045675c6","details":{"body":"<p>Rebecca Harris was Government Whip (Lord Commissioner of HM Treasury) from 9 January 2018 to 5 July 2024. Rebecca was an Assistant Government Whip in the House of Commons from June 2017 to January 2018.</p>\n\n<p>She was elected Conservative MP for Castle Point in May 2010.</p>\n","image":null},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-07-18T09:54:03Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Rebecca Harris MP","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/rebecca-harris","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","base_path":"/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","content_id":"dd4e6468-e7a9-4259-8524-29599794c2b7","details":{"body":"\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":4,"whip_organisation":{"label":"House of Commons","sort_order":1}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T20:45:41Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-07-05T11:42:36Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Rebecca Harris - Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"f3c8c46a-1ba0-40dd-a69f-ad20dcd2f04e","details":{"current":false,"ended_on":"2022-07-07T00:00:00+01:00","person_appointment_order":7165,"started_on":"2021-09-17T00:00:00+01:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/marcus-jones","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/marcus-jones","base_path":"/government/people/marcus-jones","content_id":"ad85f664-e99f-4408-88a8-1394e829d647","details":{"body":"<p>Marcus Jones was Treasurer of His Majesty’s Household (Deputy Chief Whip) from 27 October 2022 to 5 July 2024.</p>\n\n<p>He was previously Minister of State at the Department for Levelling Up, Housing and Communities between 7 July 2022 and 7 September 2022.</p>\n\n<p>He was previously Vice Chamberlain of HM Household (Government Whip) from 13 February 2020, Assistant Government Whip from 29 July 2019 to 13 February 2020 and Parliamentary Under Secretary of State (Minister for Local Government) from May 2015 to January 2018.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"education\">Education</h2>\n\n<p>Marcus attended St Thomas More School, Nuneaton, followed by King Edward VI College.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"political-career\">Political career</h2>\n\n<p>He has previously served as the Parliamentary Private Secretary to the Financial Secretary to the Treasury and Parliamentary Private Secretary to the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport. He was the Conservative MP for Nuneaton from 2010 to 2024.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"career-outside-politics\">Career outside politics</h2>\n\n<p>Prior to his election to parliament, Marcus was a councillor on Nuneaton and Bedworth Borough Council, serving as leader of the Conservative Group from 2006 to 2009 and leader of the council. He stood down as council leader in 2009.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"personal-life\">Personal life</h2>\n\n<p>Marcus is married to Suzanne and they have a son, Oliver, and daughter, Martha.</p>\n\n<p>He has a number of hobbies including football and has played for a number of local Sunday league teams in the Nuneaton and district league. He is a supporter of Coventry City FC and enjoys angling on the rare occasion when he has spare time.</p>\n\n","image":{"alt_text":"The Rt Hon Marcus Jones","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5a4f63e440f0b648c7221489/s465_Marcus_Jones_-_Official_960x640.jpg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-07-18T09:53:48Z","schema_name":"person","title":"The Rt Hon Marcus Jones","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/marcus-jones","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","base_path":"/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","content_id":"dd4e6468-e7a9-4259-8524-29599794c2b7","details":{"body":"\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":4,"whip_organisation":{"label":"House of Commons","sort_order":1}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T20:45:41Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2022-07-07T20:11:09Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Marcus Jones MP - Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"668cba05-a1dc-4e50-a263-ccd94013ebe5","details":{"current":false,"ended_on":"2021-09-17T00:00:00+01:00","person_appointment_order":5940,"started_on":"2019-12-17T00:00:00+00:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/mike-freer","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/mike-freer","base_path":"/government/people/mike-freer","content_id":"4202c431-908f-4029-a26c-b5fa267231eb","details":{"body":"<p>Mike Freer was Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for the Ministry of Justice between 20 September 2022 and 5 July 2024.</p>\n\n<p>He was Minister for Exports and Minister for Equalities between September 2021 and 6 July 2022.</p>\n\n<p>He was a Member of Parliament for Finchley and Golders Green from 2010 to 2024. Mike was Assistant Government Whip between June 2017 and July 2018. He was also Lord Commissioner of the Treasury from July 2018 to December 2019 and served as Comptroller of HM Household from December 2019 to September 2021.</p>\n","image":{"alt_text":"Mike Freer","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/614c2d9b8fa8f561075cadcd/s465_Mike-Freer.jpg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-07-18T10:27:48Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Mike Freer","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/mike-freer","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","base_path":"/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","content_id":"dd4e6468-e7a9-4259-8524-29599794c2b7","details":{"body":"\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":4,"whip_organisation":{"label":"House of Commons","sort_order":1}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T20:45:41Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2021-09-17T15:59:21Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Mike Freer MP - Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"65fd2b4a-a459-4295-ac15-f6731b5e482b","details":{"current":false,"ended_on":"2019-12-16T00:00:00+00:00","person_appointment_order":5648,"started_on":"2019-07-28T00:00:00+01:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/jeremy-quin","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/jeremy-quin","base_path":"/government/people/jeremy-quin","content_id":"35581511-38d0-46bf-ac08-a4ccc7ab8528","details":{"body":"<p>Jeremy Quin was previously Paymaster General and Minister for the Cabinet Office between 25 October 2022 and 13 November 2023.</p>\n\n<p>He was Minister of State (Minister for Crime, Policing and Fire) at the Home Office between 7 September 2022 and 25 October 2022.</p>\n\n<p>He was Minister of State (Minister for Defence Procurement) at the Ministry of Defence between 13 February 2020 and 7 September 2022.</p>\n\n<p>In December 2019, Jeremy became Parliamentary Secretary in the Cabinet Office with responsibilities for the Government Commercial Function and other cross-government programmes.</p>\n\n<p>In July 2018, Jeremy accepted a role in the Government as a member of the Whips’ Office and was promoted to serve as a senior Whip (as “Comptroller of Her Majesty’s Household”) in July 2019.</p>\n\n<p>In 2008 to 2009, he served on secondment as senior corporate finance adviser to HM Treasury, assisting them on the UK’s response to the financial crisis.</p>\n\n<p>Before entering politics, Jeremy worked in corporate finance for 25 years latterly as Managing Director of Deutsche Bank.</p>\n\n","image":{"alt_text":"The Rt Hon Jeremy Quin","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/635b97908fa8f5653ba074dc/s465_Untitled.jpg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-05-30T12:06:58Z","schema_name":"person","title":"The Rt Hon Jeremy Quin","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/jeremy-quin","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","base_path":"/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","content_id":"dd4e6468-e7a9-4259-8524-29599794c2b7","details":{"body":"\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":4,"whip_organisation":{"label":"House of Commons","sort_order":1}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T20:45:41Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2019-12-16T21:07:54Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Jeremy Quin - Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"274283fd-6b51-4141-9b21-0546a03b22a4","details":{"current":false,"ended_on":"2019-07-25T00:00:00+01:00","person_appointment_order":4945,"started_on":"2018-07-25T00:00:00+01:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/mark-spencer","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/mark-spencer","base_path":"/government/people/mark-spencer","content_id":"6f86fea0-0c83-4518-8a1d-b171d31e63ff","details":{"body":"<p>In March 2024, Mark was appointed as a Kings Batchelor by His Majesty the King, creating Sir Mark Spencer, the Rt Hon Member for Sherwood.</p>\n\n<p>Mark Spencer was Minister of State at the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs from September 2022 to July 2024.</p>\n\n<p>He was previously Lord President and Leader of the House of Commons from 8 February 2022 to 6 September 2022. He was Parliamentary Secretary to the Treasury (Chief Whip) between July 2019 and February 2022, Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) between July 2018 and July 2019, and Vice Chamberlain of HM Household (Government Whip) between January and July 2018. He was Junior Lord of the Treasury (Government Whip) from June 2017 to January 2018. He was an Assistant Government Whip from 17 July 2016 to 15 June 2017.</p>\n\n<p>Mark was the Conservative MP for Sherwood from 2010 to 2024.</p>\n","image":{"alt_text":"The Rt Hon Sir Mark Spencer","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d42fee540f0b66182a90670/s465_Mark_Spencer.jpg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-07-16T08:13:00Z","schema_name":"person","title":"The Rt Hon Sir Mark Spencer","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/mark-spencer","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","base_path":"/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","content_id":"dd4e6468-e7a9-4259-8524-29599794c2b7","details":{"body":"\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":4,"whip_organisation":{"label":"House of Commons","sort_order":1}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T20:45:41Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2019-11-06T00:12:57Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"The Rt Hon Mark Spencer - Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"07ad69f8-ef58-46de-927a-f4c78eaeccbf","details":{"current":false,"ended_on":"2018-07-09T00:00:00+01:00","person_appointment_order":4550,"started_on":"2018-01-09T00:00:00+00:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/chris-heaton-harris","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/chris-heaton-harris","base_path":"/government/people/chris-heaton-harris","content_id":"c219702c-084f-4fc5-a89c-e9b1b28ad489","details":{"body":"<p>Chris Heaton-Harris was Secretary of State for Northern Ireland between 6 September 2022 and 5 July 2024.</p>\n\n<p>He was previously Parliamentary Secretary to the Treasury (Chief Whip) from 8 February 2022 to 6 September 2022.</p>\n\n<p>He was Minister of State at the Foreign, Commonwealth &amp; Development Office from 19 December 2021 to 8 February 2022.</p>\n\n<p>He was previously appointed Minister of State at the Department for Transport on 25 July 2019. He was previously a Parliamentary Under Secretary of State at the Department for Exiting the European Union from July 2018 to April 2019.</p>\n\n<p>Previously he was Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) from 9 January 2018 to 9 July 2018. Chris was previously Vice Chamberlain of HM Household (Government Whip) from June 2017 to January 2018.</p>\n\n<p>He was made an Assistant Government Whip in July 2016. He was the Conservative MP for Daventry from 2010 to 2024.</p>\n","image":{"alt_text":"The Rt Hon Chris Heaton-Harris","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5e4695a1ed915d4ffa3982a5/s465_960-chris-heaton-harris-mp.jpg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-07-18T10:00:20Z","schema_name":"person","title":"The Rt Hon Chris Heaton-Harris","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/chris-heaton-harris","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","base_path":"/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","content_id":"dd4e6468-e7a9-4259-8524-29599794c2b7","details":{"body":"\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":4,"whip_organisation":{"label":"House of Commons","sort_order":1}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T20:45:41Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/comptroller-of-hm-household-government-whip","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2019-11-06T00:12:53Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Chris Heaton-Harris - Comptroller of HM Household (Government Whip) ","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","phase":"live","public_updated_at":"2026-05-12T21:45:41+01:00","publishing_app":"whitehall","publishing_request_id":"21-17